A new Festival of Ideas in arts, humanities and social sciences will take place in Cambridge, from 22 October to 2 November 2008, organised by the University of Cambridge, involving numerous museums and departments, and collaborating with several educational and community partners.  Please see website for full details.  Most events are free and do not require booking, but there is a charge for a few events and some events also need booking in advance.  Events are at locations throughout Cambridge.

GENERATIONS is a community play bringing together local people aged 13-18 and over 55 to make a musical theatre production to be performed at the Civic Hall, Ellesmere Port on July 31st and August 1st 2009. GENERATIONS will explore age, and what we think it is to be young and what it means to be old, inspired by grandparent and grandchild relationships. Made possible through support from Shell UK and the Education Improvement Partnership through the Big Lottery,The Big Lottery Fund distributes half of all National Lottery good causes funding across the UK.  The Fund aims to enable others to make real improvements to the lives of disadvantaged people and the wellbeing of communities, through fair and open funding of people, projects and programmes.

Tiverton Family Festival is a series of events throughout the week beginning the 19th October. There will be workshops in and out of schools during the week, events at the museum and the BMX track on the Saturday, and a Family Fun day on Sunday 25th October. All events are free, but some will require booking. More details on workshops available soon (contact jgoddard@tiverton-st-johns-primary.devon.sch.uk)

Come to our weekly session for children aged 12 months to 5 years and their carers. The session involves soft play, rhyme time, play materials and refreshments. Please note that places are limited and booking is required.
Cost: Adults £5 (Concessions £3) - receive year round entry. Under 16s free plus and additional 50p
